SIMPLE: next
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Next
<hw>Next</hw> <pr>(n⟦ecr⟧kst)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>, <pos>superl.</pos> of
<er>Nigh</er>. <ety>[AS. <ets>n⟦emac⟧hst</ets>,
<ets>ni⟦eacute⟧hst</ets>, <ets>n⟦ymac⟧hst</ets>, superl. of
<ets>ne⟦aacute⟧h</ets> nigh. See <er>Nigh</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Nearest in place; having no similar object intervening.</def>
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Her princely guest⟦br⟧
Was <qex>next</qex> her side; in order sat the rest.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Fear followed me so hard, that I fled the <qex>next</qex> way.</q>
<rj><qau>Bunyan.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Nearest in time; <as>as, the <ex>next</ex> day or
hour</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Adjoining in a series; immediately preceding or
following in order.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>None could tell whose turn should be the <qex>next</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Gay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Nearest in degree, quality, rank, right, or
relation; <as>as, the <ex>next</ex> heir was an infant</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The man is near of kin unto us, one of our <qex>next</qex>
kinsmen.</q> <rj><qau>Ruth ii. 20.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ <xex>Next</xex> is usually followed by <xex>to</xex>
before an object, but <xex>to</xex> is sometimes omitted. In such cases
<xex>next</xex> in considered by many grammarians as a
preposition.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Next friend</b></col> <fld>(Law)</fld>, <cd>one who
represents an infant, a married woman, or any person who can not appear
<xex>sui juris</xex>, in a suit at law.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Next</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Next
<hw>Next</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>In the time, place, or order nearest
or immediately succeeding; <as>as, this man follows
<ex>next</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nexus</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
